-- Nomura’s Matsuzawa Tops Nikkei Bond-Analyst Rankings
-- B y   M o n a m i   Y u i   a n d   K a z u m i   M i u r a
-- 2012-04-02T00:14:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/nomura-s-matsuzawa-tops-nikkei-bond-analyst-rankings.html
Naka Matsuzawa, chief strategist at
Nomura Securities Co. in Tokyo, was chosen as the top analyst
for Japanese bonds in a survey of institutional investors by
Nikkei Veritas for a second-straight year.  Jun Ishii, chief fixed-income strategist at Mitsubishi UFJ
Morgan Stanley Securities Co. ranked second, followed by Chotaro Morita, chief fixed-income strategist in Tokyo at Barclays
Capital., the weekly financial newspaper said yesterday.  In a separate ranking, Nikkei Veritas named  Ryutaro Kono ,
chief economist at BNP Paribas SA in Tokyo, as its top-ranked
economist. The government nominated Kono on March 23 to join the
 Bank of Japan (8301) ’s policy board.  To contact the reporter on this story:
